      • processing

        <T,V> void processing(@NotNull
                      Processor<T,V> processor,
                      @Nullable
                      T dataForProcessing,
                      @NotNull
                      kotlin.jvm.functions.Function1<? super V,kotlin.Unit> onProcessedCallback,
                      @NotNull
                      kotlin.jvm.functions.Function1<? super java.lang.Exception,kotlin.Unit> onErrorCallback,
                      @NotNull
                      CALLBACK_IN callbackIn)

        Processing dataForProcessing with the help of a implementation interface Processor the result is returned by calling onProcessedCallback the error is returned by calling onErrorCallback

        Parameters:
        processor - instance off class that implements interface Processor that processes data
        dataForProcessing - data for processing data interpretation dependson the implementation interface Processor
        onProcessedCallback - the code that return the result,if this code is missing will be run stubthe result can be passed to the next task for processing seeclass DELIVER_.TO_NEXT
        onErrorCallback - the code that handle the Exception,if this code is missing will be run stubErrorCallback
        callbackIn - specifies where the callback is performed,see enum CALLBACK_IN
        See Also:
        dataForProcessing, interface Processor, onProcessedCallback, onErrorCallback
